    "body": "Unsure if this is a bug per se... It does change the external environment, so this is sort of expected? I can't really imagine a case where you would use the same env var with different values in a test run, especially not one where you set the env var using `vm.setEnv`. Re: `vm.setFork` you don't need to use `vm.env` to get that from the environment, you can just use env var interpolation in `foundry.toml`",
